tweet_text: onchain identity gets tricky in a multichain world                                                                                                                                                                       thats where clustersxyz is trying to come into the picture   excited by the crosschain future but not psyched by the disparate nature of determining which wallet belongs to your buddies on every network  clusters is a new crosschain name service built by delegatedotxyz and layerzero_labs which lets users bid on and register wallet names that work across ethereum and nonethereum chains simultaneously the pitch all the chains all your wallets one name  how is this different than ens  clusters is in the same general ballpark as the ethereum name service ens as both protocols offer humanreadable blockchain domains with multichain support  where these projects fundamentally differ is their architecture  for its part ens uses a custom multichain address resolution system within its protocol to enable ens names to record and point to addresses on different blockchains  in contrast clusters is the first app built on the new v2 version of layerzero an interoperability protocol designed to let projects operate across different blockchains seamlessly and securely  how clusters fights squatting  to discourage domain squatting clusters makes use of a mechanism known as demandbased recurring pricing which vitalikbuterin has previously written about  so while ens relies on fixedrate renewal feeseg 5year for fivecharacter domainsclusters adjusts renewal fees based on market demand  this model allows anyone to bid on a domain to raise its annual fee if the bids remain for a long period of time  the renewal fee then becomes a percentage of this floating valuation encouraging domain owners to either accept high bids or pay increased fees as a squatting mitigation  the open beta has arrived  on february 1st 2024 clusters kicked off its beta launch with the introduction of its auction system  during this beta phase participants can start bidding on highly soughtafter names  the highest bidders will be awarded their desired domains ensuring transparency  clusters is also developing a refund system for unsuccessful bidders so people who come up emptyhanded can get their money back  additionally clusters has created a boost multiplier system to accompany its auctions  in other words ownership of the corresponding ens domain possession of the relevant twitter handle and activity on social media can significantly enhance your bid giving you a competitive edge for your target name  following the beta clusters plans to finalize its auction mechanism and transition to a fully open firstcome firstserve fcfs registration system  this shift is expected to occur within the next few months  how to get started with clusters  before you can dive into clusters youll need some eth set aside for bidding on your name of choice once youve got your funds prepared you would follow these steps to proceed  1 head to clustersxyz and connect your wallet  2 click create bid at the top of the page and input your target cluster name  3 in the ensuing interface input your desired bid amountfor reference many people have been bidding in the 002006 eth range so far  4 press claim and confirm the deposit transaction with your wallet  5 start customizing your cluster by importing your profile picture from twitter and adding in additional wallets  6 press finalize setup when youre done customizing to complete the configuration process  at this point you can head over to the my profile tab on the clusters website to track your bids edit your wallet or copy your bespoke referral link to share on social media for the boosting multiplier  if any of your bids dont end up winning watch out for the launch of clusters refund system in the coming weeks  the big picture  the clusters vision is secure and userfriendly crosschain identity management  by combining auctions demandbased pricing and boost multipliers clusters is aiming to bridge the gaps between different chains in a streamlined way  going forward be sure to keep your eyes peeled as the project adds support for additional chains eg networks in the cosmos ecosystem  article by wpeaster

tweet_raw: #SaitaScholarsToday we have a Beginners Guide to Etherscan.Welcome to the world of Ethereum and decentralized finance (DeFi)! Etherscan is your window into the Ethereum blockchain offering valuable insights and tools for navigating this decentralized ecosystem. Heres a beginners guide to help you get started:What is Etherscan?Etherscan is a blockchain explorer specifically designed for Ethereum. It allows users to explore the Ethereum blockchain view transactions smart contracts token transfers and more.How to Access Etherscan:Simply visit etherscan.io on your web browser. You can access various features and tools without the need to create an account.Understanding Etherscan Features:Search Bar: Enter Ethereum addresses transaction hashes or token names to explore specific details.Blocks: View the latest blocks mined on the Ethereum blockchain and their associated transactions.Transactions: Explore individual transactions by entering their transaction hashes.Tokens: Discover ERC-20 tokens and their associated smart contracts.Address Details: Get insights into Ethereum addresses including transaction history token holdings and smart contract interactions.Smart Contracts: Explore the code and interactions of smart contracts deployed on the Ethereum blockchain.Using Etherscan Safely:Etherscan is a powerful tool but exercise caution when exploring transactions and smart contracts. Be wary of phishing links or scams that may redirect you to malicious websites.Always verify the URL and use secure browsing practices.Why Etherscan Matters:Etherscan provides transparency and visibility into the Ethereum blockchain empowering users to track transactions monitor token movements and verify smart contract interactions.Its an essential tool for investors developers and anyone interested in understanding the Ethereum ecosystem.Further Learning:Dive deeper into Etherscans advanced features such as contract verification token analytics and blockchain statistics.Stay updated with the latest developments in Ethereum and blockchain technology.With Etherscan as your guide youre ready to explore the vast landscape of Ethereum and decentralized applications. tweet_text: vitalik buterin and the ethereum foundation explore five strategies to reduce the maximum block size   ethereum cofounder vitalikbuterin and the ethereum foundation are actively considering measures to optimize the blockchains efficiency particularly focusing on the rollupcentric roadmap   key points  block gas limit challenge   the blog post discusses challenges related to the ethereum gas limit which regulates the maximum gas spent executing transactions or smart contracts in each block   the objective is to find solutions that increase the gas limit without compromising security  solutions to reduce maximum block size   five potential solutions are proposed ranging in complexity to increase block gas limits and discourage the use of calldata to reduce maximum block size and variance   due to calldatas gas consumption the network is overloaded so solutions are being sought to increase the gas limit  proposed strategies   one proposed solution involves a straightforward increase in the calldata cost from 16 to 42 gas effectively reducing the maximum block size from 178 megabytes to 068 megabytes   another approach suggests increasing calldata cost while decreasing other opcode costs aiming to strike a balance in optimizing blockchain functionality  calddata fee market and evm loyalty bonus   further creating a separate calldata fee market similar to data blobs is suggested to potentially increase gas limits with pricing adjusting based on demand   another intriguing idea involves introducing an evm loyalty bonus to compensate calldataheavy apps promoting a fair and efficient ecosystem  evaluating tradeoffs   the considerations involve evaluating tradeoffs between simplicity and effectiveness with some proposals deemed potentially too blunt or adding excessive complexity   the final decision aims to strike a balance that optimizes blockchain performance without compromising essential functionalities  image forbes eth cryptonews vitalik
tweet_raw: VITALIK BUTERIN AND THE ETHEREUM FOUNDATION EXPLORE FIVE STRATEGIES TO REDUCE THE MAXIMUM BLOCK SIZE- Ethereum co-founder @VitalikButerin and the #Ethereum Foundation are actively considering measures to optimize the blockchains efficiency particularly focusing on the rollup-centric roadmap. Key Points:BLOCK GAS LIMIT CHALLENGE:- The blog post discusses challenges related to the Ethereum gas limit which regulates the maximum gas spent executing transactions or smart contracts in each block.- The objective is to find solutions that increase the gas limit without compromising security.SOLUTIONS TO REDUCE MAXIMUM BLOCK SIZE:- Five potential solutions are proposed ranging in complexity to increase block gas limits and discourage the use of calldata to reduce maximum block size and variance.- Due to Calldatas gas consumption the network is overloaded so solutions are being sought to increase the gas limit.PROPOSED STRATEGIES:- One proposed solution involves a straightforward increase in the calldata cost from 16 to 42 gas effectively reducing the maximum block size from 1.78 megabytes to 0.68 megabytes.- Another approach suggests increasing calldata cost while decreasing other opcode costs aiming to strike a balance in optimizing blockchain functionality.CALDDATA FEE MARKET AND EVM LOYALTY BONUS:- Further creating a separate calldata fee market similar to data blobs is suggested to potentially increase gas limits with pricing adjusting based on demand.- Another intriguing idea involves introducing an EVM loyalty bonus to compensate calldata-heavy apps promoting a fair and efficient ecosystem.EVALUATING TRADE-OFFS:- The considerations involve evaluating trade-offs between simplicity and effectiveness with some proposals deemed potentially too blunt or adding excessive complexity.- The final decision aims to strike a balance that optimizes blockchain performance without compromising essential functionalities.Image: Forbes#ETH #CryptoNews #Vitalik

tweet_raw: Hello all space catdets! We just posted 3 major updates to the launchpool Jupiter DAO and LFG candidates!Launchpool Updates- 90M JUP tokens have been withdrawn sent to the cold multisig and taken out of circulation- USDC will be withdrawn in $10M batches with the first batch completed.- The remaining USDC will be removed gradually over the next few months.This will allow JUP to regain price discovery while assuring all participants that the team is committed to a long-term gradual withdrawal of USDC liquidity.Jupiter DAOWe believe the Jupiter DAO can be the most dynamic active and forward looking DAO in crypto with the mandate of growing Jupiter Solana and the meta. To encourage participation and to fund it with the capital to pursue important initiatives:- 75% of future LFG launchpad fees will be distributed to governance participants.- 75% of future DLMM launchpool fees will be allocated to the DAO- The DAO will start with 100M in JUP earned from the LFG launchpad for voting incentives and 6.15M in operational funds from JUP Launch.Over the next month we will starting the community process to form not only the DAO but also the ecosystem working group and the official catdet role!Potential LFG CandidatesThe goal of LFG is to grow the ecosystem pie by helping good projects tap into a wider community and ecosystem. It is crucial to understand that the community and DAO collectively decides on each launch and the team does not decide on which projects are launched on LFG.To kickstart the process:- We have brought three potential LFG launches to the DAO: Sanctum Debridge and SharkyFi.- We will organize introductions to these projects so that the community can make a decision on the first LFG launch.LFG is meant to be as open and community driven as possible. For other projects that wish to be involved there will also be a channel to apply as well so please keep a lookout for that as well!Theres going to be a lot to do in February to get ready for the next phase of Jupiter so stay tuned!For full details and context read this tweet!

tweet_raw: Hello all space catdets! We just posted 3 major updates to the launchpool Jupiter DAO and LFG candidates!Launchpool Updates- 90M JUP tokens have been withdrawn sent to the cold multisig and taken out of circulation- USDC will be withdrawn in $10M batches with the first batch completed.- The remaining USDC will be removed gradually over the next few months.This will allow JUP to regain price discovery while assuring all participants that the team is committed to a long-term gradual withdrawal of USDC liquidity.Jupiter DAOWe believe the Jupiter DAO can be the most dynamic active and forward looking DAO in crypto with the mandate of growing Jupiter Solana and the meta. To encourage participation and to fund it with the capital to pursue important initiatives:- 75% of future LFG launchpad fees will be distributed to governance participants.- 75% of future DLMM launchpool fees will be allocated to the DAO- The DAO will start with 100M in JUP earned from the LFG launchpad for voting incentives and 6.15M in operational funds from JUP Launch.Over the next month we will starting the community process to form not only the DAO but also the ecosystem working group and the official catdet role!Potential LFG CandidatesThe goal of LFG is to grow the ecosystem pie by helping good projects tap into a wider community and ecosystem. It is crucial to understand that the community and DAO collectively decides on each launch and the team does not decide on which projects are launched on LFG.To kickstart the process:- We have brought three potential LFG launches to the DAO: Sanctum Debridge and SharkyFi.- We will organize introductions to these projects so that the community can make a decision on the first LFG launch.LFG is meant to be as open and community driven as possible. For other projects that wish to be involved there will also be a channel to apply as well so please keep a lookout for that as well!Theres going to be a lot to do in February to get ready for the next phase of Jupiter so stay tuned!For full details and context read this tweet!

tweet_text: the cone nebula from hubble image credit hubble legacy archive nasa esa  processing  licence judy schmidt  explanation stars are forming in the gigantic dust pillar called the cone nebula cones pillars and majestic flowing shapes abound in stellar nurseries where natal clouds of gas and dust are buffeted by energetic winds from newborn stars the cone nebula a wellknown example lies within the bright galactic starforming region ngc 2264 the cone was captured in unprecedented detail in this closeup composite of several observations from the earthorbiting hubble space telescope while the cone nebula about 2500 lightyears away in monoceros is around 7 lightyears long the region pictured here surrounding the cones blunted head is a mere 25 lightyears across in our neck of the galaxy that distance is just over half way from our sun to its nearest stellar neighbors in the alpha centauri star system the massive star ngc 2264 irs seen by hubbles infrared camera in 1997 is the likely source of the wind sculpting the cone nebula and lies off the top of the image the cone nebulas reddish veil is produced by dust and glowing hydrogen gas
tweet_raw: The Cone Nebula from HubbleImage Credit: Hubble Legacy Archive NASA ESA - Processing & Licence: Judy SchmidtExplanation: Stars are forming in the gigantic dust pillar called the Cone Nebula. Cones pillars and majestic flowing shapes abound in stellar nurseries where natal clouds of gas and dust are buffeted by energetic winds from newborn stars. The Cone Nebula a well-known example lies within the bright galactic star-forming region NGC 2264. The Cone was captured in unprecedented detail in this close-up composite of several observations from the Earth-orbiting Hubble Space Telescope. While the Cone Nebula about 2500 light-years away in Monoceros is around 7 light-years long the region pictured here surrounding the cones blunted head is a mere 2.5 light-years across. In our neck of the galaxy that distance is just over half way from our Sun to its nearest stellar neighbors in the Alpha Centauri star system. The massive star NGC 2264 IRS seen by Hubbles infrared camera in 1997 is the likely source of the wind sculpting the Cone Nebula and lies off the top of the image. The Cone Nebulas reddish veil is produced by dust and glowing hydrogen gas.
